Beyoncé’s accomplishments include, being 5x Oscar nominated, performing for the Oscar’s 3x, 8 Primetime Emmy Nominations. Beyoncé has officially become the most awarded Artist of ALL TIME. Now to her statistical musical accolades, Beyonce is the first female artist to have all 7 of her solo studio albums debut at No1 on the Billboard 200. Beyoncé is the first woman and only the third performer ever, outside of Paul McCartney and Michael Jackson, to have at least 20 Top 10 songs as a solo artist and at least 10 Top 10 songs on the Billboard Hot 100. Her 2nd Album Bday produced 4 top 10 hits and ‘check up on it’ which topped at No1 for 5 weeks. Her fifth album ‘Beyonce’ became the fastest-selling album ever on iTunes, both in the US and worldwide after just 3 days of sales.

At 41 and after a 6 year absence, her latest album Renaissance was the second biggest 2022 album debut by a female artist and the third-biggest overall.
